=Description=

Josef Davies-Coates:

The “[[Democracy Experiment]]”, DemoEx is Direct Democracy Political Party in Sweden that enables members to propose and vote on policies. Your Party http://www.yourparty.org was a similar effort in the UK back in 2004 (although the law here means members cannot dictate how their councillor or MP, if elected, votes - and the site is now down). Mikael Nordfors (author of [[Democracy 2.1]]) was involved with this project but they eventually adopted a non-delegative voting system.


